y_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java implementation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the setup silently ignores exceptions, and if the factory is configured correctly, it should work with the class implementation. The default factory isn't public, and I'm considering how the ClassLoader can load it while the newInstance method from ForkJoinPool can access it. That’s not the usual public API process. I wonder if I should put the Java helper in the test package and update the user-code-filter accordingly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jbG9b1iQq7ZQXrphnDT1ozoG|fc_05d5064b75f123d8016a10499c066c81a29a27ad354ea0eaa1", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_library/ScalaConcurrentForkjoinForkJoinPoolTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scala_lang.scala_library\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\nimport scala.concurrent.ExecutionContext\nimport scala.concurrent.Future\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\n\nclass ScalaConcurrentForkjoinForkJoinPoolTest {\n  @Test\n  def initializesForkJoinPoolWithConfiguredCommonPoolClasses(): Unit = {\n    val factoryPropertyName: String = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.threadFactory\"\n    val handlerPropertyName: String = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.exceptionHandler\"\n    val parallelismPropertyName: String = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.parallelism\"\n    val defaultFactoryClassName: String = \"scala.concurrent.forkjoin.ForkJoinPool$DefaultForkJoinWorkerThreadFactory\"\n    val instantiableScalaClassName: String = \"scala.concurrent.forkjoin.ForkJoinPool\"\n\n    val previousFactoryProperty: String = System.getProperty(factoryPropertyName)\n    val previousHandlerProperty: String = System.getProperty(handlerPropertyName)\n    val previousParallelismProperty: String = System.getProperty(parallelismPropertyName)\n\n    System.setProperty(factoryPropertyName, defaultFactoryClassName)\n    System.setProperty(handlerPropertyName, instantiableScalaClassName)\n    System.setProperty(parallelismPropertyName, \"1\")\n\n    try {\n      implicit val executionContext: ExecutionContext = ExecutionContext.global\n      val workerThreadName: String = Await.result(Future(Thread.currentThread().getName), 10.seconds)\n\n      assertThat(workerThreadName).isNotEmpty\n    } finally {\n      restoreProperty(factoryPropertyName, previousFactoryProperty)\n      restoreProperty(handlerPropertyName, previousHandlerProperty)\n      restoreProperty(parallelismPropertyName, previousParallelismProperty)\n    }\n  }\n\n  private def restoreProperty(name: String, value: String): Unit = {\n    if (value == null) {\n      System.clearProperty(name)\n    } else {\n      System.setProperty(name, value)\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1743, "output": 1970, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38017, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779452293489, "responseId": "resp_05d5064b75f123d8016a10498632fc81a2a0035d5cfead6ecb"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_jbG9b1iQq7ZQXrphnDT1ozoG|fc_05d5064b75f123d8016a10499c066c81a29a27ad354ea0eaa1", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2215 bytes to tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_library/ScalaConcurrentForkjoinForkJoinPoolTest.scala"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779452319382}]}
